    <fr:title text="Multivariate Normal Distribution">Multivariate Normal Distribution</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
    The multivariate normal distribution is defined by the density function
          <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[f(\mathbf {x}) = (2\pi )^{-k/2}\operatorname *{det}(\mathbf {\Sigma })^{-1/2}\ \exp \left (-\frac {1}{2}(\mathbf {x}-{\boldsymbol {\mu }})^{\mathrm {{T}}}{\boldsymbol {\Sigma }}^{-1}\big (\mathbf {x}-{\boldsymbol {\mu }}\big )\right )]]></fr:tex>
    where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ \mathbf {\Sigma } ]]></fr:tex> is the covariance matrix <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {\Sigma }_{i,j} = \mathbb {E}[(X_i - \mu _i)(X_j - \mu _j)^{\top }]]]></fr:tex>and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ \boldsymbol {\mu } ]]></fr:tex> is the mean vector <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbf {\mu } = (\mathbb {E}[X_1], \ldots , \mathbb {E}[X_n])]]></fr:tex>.
  </html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
